sk client to lie supine or sit back in chair with head slightly hyper extended</label><item><label>Done</label><value>done</value></item><item><label>Not Done</label><value>not</value></item></select1><select1 appearance="list-nolabel" ref="/data/intro/step8"><label>Arrange supplies at bedside and apply gloves</label><item><label>Done</label><value>done</value></item><item><label>Not Done</label><value>not</value></item></select1><select1 appearance="list-nolabel" ref="/data/intro/step9"><label>If crusts or drainages are present , along eyelid margins or inner canthus , gently wash away . soak crusts thata re dried and difficult to remove by applying damp wash cloth or cotton ball over eye for few minutes . always wipe and clean inner to outer canthus</label><item><label>Done</label><value>done</value></item><item><label>Not Done</label><value>not</value></item></select1><select1 appearance="list-nolabel" ref="/data/intro/step10"><label>Hold cotton ball or clean tissue in non dominant hand on client cheek bones just below lower eyelids</label><item><label>Done</label><value>done</value></item><item><label>Not Done</label><value>not</value></item></select1><select1 appearance="list-nolabel" ref="/data/intro/step11"><label>With tissue or coton , resting on lower lid , gently press downward with thumb or forefinger against bony orbit</label><item><label>Done</label><value>done</value></item><item><label>Not Done</label><value>not</value></item></select1><select1 appearance="list-nolabel" ref="/data/intro/step12"><label>Ask client to look at ceiling</label><item><label>Done</label><value>done</value></item><item><label>Not Done</label><value>not</value></item></select1><select1 appearance="list-nolabel" ref="/data/intro/step13"><label>Instill eye drop

-With dominant hand resting on client forehead , hold filled medication , eye dropper approximately 1-2 cm above conjuctival sac 

-Drop prescribed number of drops of medication into conjuctival sac 

-1If client blinks or closes eye or if drops hand on outer lid margin , repeat procedure 

-After administering medication that cause systemic effects , protect your finger with clean tissue and pply gentle pressure to client nasolacrimal duct for 30 to 6o secs</label><item><label>Done</label><value>done</value></item><item><label>Not Done</label><value>not</value></item></select1><select1 appearance="list-nolabel" ref="/data/intro/step14"><label>Instill eye ointment 

